cs.LG, cs.SE, cs.AI, cs.PL, cs.SY

The paper is about developing a framework for machine learning solutions that minimizes human intervention. This involves templatizing machine learning algorithms, sharing code and computation between different algorithms, and employing hierarchical and heuristic based pruning to reduce the search space. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves programming by Sketching and Partial Evaluation, which falls under the sub-category cs.SE (Software Engineering). Additionally, the paper deals with the use of algorithms and heuristics, which are relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves templatizing algorithms, which falls under the sub-category cs.PL (Programming Languages). Finally, the paper involves the use of heuristics to reduce the search space, which is relevant to cs.SY (Systems and Control).
